desc: You must visit this viral valley in China this 2024 🏮 This is📍Wangxian Valley, Jiangxi, China, a newly built scenic spot inspired by the Chinese ancient town architecture. This might not be a real ancient town but is a perfect place to travel in China for documenting, taking photos and fly your drone. How to get there? 🚄 2.5 hours Shanghai to Shangrao + 1 hour by car 🏨 Only two hotels inside the scenic area and more options at the nearest town. 💲Entrance ticket is 100rmb 🕣 Open hours 8:00-22:00 ☀️Best time to go: Spring and autumn, during summer can be very hot and crowded. Also avoid national holidays. 🏩 Looking for hotels? Send me a DM and l share the hotel I stayed at (no collaborations) and other options for foreigners. desc: 3 old towns in China that you must visit in 2024🏮 pt1 What to know 👇 -Nanxun Old Town is a beautiful water town not far from Shanghai. Is perfect for a weekend trip.  You can stop one night in Huzhou to experience the free fireworks show on Friday and Saturday. - Furong Old Town, is the famous waterfall village. Spend one night at this place to experience the lantern decorations. - Fenghuang Old Town, is one of the most beautiful old towns in China. I recommend staying two days and one night at least to experience the local life. * I often recommend visiting Furong & Fenghuang in combination with Zhangjiajie. Link in my bio if you want to sign up for my travel guide covering Zhangjiajie.  Do you still have questions? desc: My first 2024 spring season travel. But why Yunnan? Yunnan ( 云南), the most southwestern province in China, is rich in UNESCO World Heritage Sites like the Old Town of Lijiang. You can enjoy a breathtaking natural views almost everywhere and I especially enjoyed the magical Tiger Leaping George and Dali. Besides that, you can also explore snow capped year round, Jade Dragon Snow Mountain in Lijiang. Yunnan is noted for its extraordinary mix of ethnic groups.
